-- IP Group to buy remaining 80 pct stake in Fusion IP
-- By Roshni Menon in Bangalore
-- Thu Jan 23, 2014 02:33AM EST
-- None



Jan 23 (Reuters) - IP Group Plc <IPO.L> said it had agreed to buy the 80 percent stake it does not already own in Fusion IP Plc <FIP.L> for about 70 million pounds ($116.08 million) in stock.

The deal offers Fusion IP shareholders 0.446 IP Group shares for every share held, or a premium of about 27 percent to the stock's Wednesday close. [ID:nRSW3333Ya] The deal values Fusion IP at 80.2 pence per share or about 87.8 million pounds.